<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9200, 9300, 9400 Models Built After January 1, 1995 - ELECTRICAL
        TROUBLESHOOTING FANS - TROUBLESHOOTING - ENGINE COOLING FAN CONTROLS HORTON AND KYSOR W/DETROIT DIESEL SERIES 60
        DDEC III
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ENGINE COOLING FAN CONTROLS HORTON AND KYSOR W/DETROIT DIESEL SERIES 60 DDEC III</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Fan Solenoid and Circuits</title>
            <para>Refer to HORTON &#38; KYSOR ENGINE FAN W/Detroit Diesel Series 60 DDEC III circuit diagram in
                CTS-5119S.
            </para>
            <para>Before beginning this test procedure, inspect all connectors for loose or damaged pins, wires, etc.
            </para>
            <table id="t0805603" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Test 4 - Testing Fan Solenoid and Circuits</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" align="center" charoff="50" char="c">
                    <colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="4" colname="4" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="5" colname="5" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="6" colname="6" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="7" colname="7" colwidth="1.80in" colsep="1"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="sqspan1-7"/>
                    <thead valign="bottom">
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="7" spanname="sqspan1-7" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TESTING FAN SOLENOID AND CIRCUITS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Check 10A fuse F9-A for open condition. Fuse OK?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>F9-A.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse. NOTE: A blown fuse
                                    will cause fan to be engaged all the time.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off/On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect fan solenoid at connector (227). Turn key ON and measure voltage to gnd
                                    at circuit 23 of connector (227).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(227) 23 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 23 from fuse, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At solenoid side of connector (227) jumper black wire to gnd and apply 12V to red
                                    wire. Does solenoid energize?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#160;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>80 PSI</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the fan solenoid.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With (227) still disconnected, remove connector (273) from ECM. At connector (273)
                                    terminal A2 measure resistance to gnd.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(273) A2 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit 23D, between connectors (273) and (227), then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With (227) still disconnected, at connector (273) terminal A2 measure voltage to
                                    gnd.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(273) A2 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1 volt?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short in circuit 23D to unwanted voltage source, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off/On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Connect (227) to fan solenoid At connector (273) use test lead to jumper terminal
                                    A2 to gnd. Turn key ON. Does solenoid energize?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Fan solenoid and circuit checks good. Go to 5.3.2.2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 23D between connectors (273) and (227),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing A/C Compressor High Pressure Switch and Circuits</title>
            <para>Refer to HORTON &#38; KYSOR ENGINE FAN W/Detroit Diesel Series 60 DDEC III circuit diagram in
                CTS-5119S.
            </para>
            <para>Before beginning this test procedure, inspect all connectors for loose or damaged pins, wires, etc.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Perform Test 4 before performing this test.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0805605" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Test 5 - Testing A/C Compressor High Pressure Switch and Circuits</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" align="center" charoff="50" char="c">
                    <colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="4" colname="4" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="5" colname="5" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="6" colname="6" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colnum="7" colname="7" colwidth="1.80in" colsep="1"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="sqspan1-7"/>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="7" spanname="sqspan1-7" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TESTING A/C COMPRESSOR HIGH PRESSURE SWITCH AND CIRCUITS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove connector (273) from ECM. Disconnect connector (228) from A/C pressure
                                    switch. At connector (273) terminal F1, measure resistance to gnd.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(273) F1 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short to gnd in circuit 23C between connectors (273) and (228), then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With A/C pressure switch disconnected, measure resistance between switch
                                    terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>A/C pressure switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="1">
                            <entry>
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (228) measure resistance to ground at circuit 23-GB.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(228) 23-GB to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 23-GB or path to gnd at neg. battery
                                    terminal, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Connect (228) to switch. At connector (273) terminal F1, measure resistance to
                                    gnd.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(273) F1 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 23C between connectors (273) and (228),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>A/C high pressure switch and circuits check good. If you suspect that the A/C high
                                    pressure switch is not opening at the correct pressure, replace the switch and
                                    retest.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
